  "name": "Celestial Peachwood Sword",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>From blade to pommel, this sword is carved from a branch of the now-extinct celestial peach tree. The blade of this<em>+3 greater striking @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.LwQb7ryTC8FlOXgX]{Disrupting} @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.DH0kB9Wbr5pDeunX]{Holy} shortsword</em> has ancient runes that can permanently destroy the most powerful undead - if you are willing to pay the price.</p>\n<p>An undead creature of 12th level or lower that takes damage from a Strike with the sword takes @Damage[10d6[vitality]] damage (@Check[type:fortitude|dc:35|basic:true]). This damage is separate from the Strike itself and isn't included in any effect based on the Strike's damage.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">r</span> envision</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger</strong> You critically hit an undead creature with the celestial peachwood sword</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The creature must succeed at a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:35] or be destroyed. If the undead fails its saving throw and is destroyed, you suffer a backlash, taking @Damage[1d6[void]] damage per level of the destroyed undead.</p>"
    },
